ambiguity /ˌæmbɪˈɡjuːɪtɪ/

(ambiguities) 

1. N-VAR If you say that there is ambiguity in something, you mean that it is unclear or confusing, or it can be understood in more than one way. 模棱两可 

例： There is considerable ambiguity about what this part of the agreement actually means. 关于协议这一部分到底是什么意思存在着相当大的含混不清。

